Ayurvedic Glow: Skin & Hair Wellness

{/* Navigation Section */}

Ayurvedic Skin Therapy

Ancient herbal remedies for glowing, healthy skin.

Ayurvedic Hair Therapy

Natural nourishment for strong, shiny, healthy hair.

{/* Ayurvedic Insights Section */}

Charaka vs. Sushruta's Classification

Charaka: Focuses on two fundamental layers—Udakdhara (hydration) and Asrukdhara (blood circulation), aligning with modern epidermal hydration and vascular supply.

Sushruta: Describes seven layers, detailing their physiological roles in pigmentation, immunity, and regeneration.

{/* Ayurvedic vs. Modern Skin Functions */}

Ayurvedic vs. Modern Skin Functions

  • Avabhasini: Similar to the stratum corneum, responsible for skin radiance and hydration.
  • Lohita: Aligns with dermal vasculature, influencing moles and angiomas.
  • Shweta & Tamra: Role in pigmentation and immune defense, akin to melanocytes and dermal immunity.
  • Vedini: Parallels nerve endings responsible for pain and touch sensation.
  • Rohini & Mansadhara: Related to healing, regeneration, and structural support, similar to fibroblasts and collagen.
{/* Ayurvedic Disease Correlation with Modern Dermatology */}

Ayurvedic Disease Correlation with Modern Dermatology

  • Sidhma & Kilas Kushta → Pityriasis Versicolor & Vitiligo
  • Dadru & Kushtha → Ringworm & Leprosy
  • Alaji & Vidradhi → Boils & Abscess
